# CODEOWNERS.example
#
# Copy this file to .github/CODEOWNERS in your company brain repo, then
# replace the placeholder handles below with your real reviewers.
#
# What this does: GitHub reads CODEOWNERS to decide who must review changes
# to which paths. Combined with the "Require review from Code Owners" branch
# protection setting on main (see AI-OS/Guides/federation-admin-setup.md,
# step 5), it means a pull request touching a protected path cannot merge
# until a named owner approves it. This is how the schema and the shared
# SOPs are held to a higher bar than ordinary knowledge notes.
#
# Syntax: a path pattern, then one or more owners (@handle or @org/team).
# Later matches win, so put the most specific rules last.
# Handles must be users or teams with at least read access to the repo.

# Default owner for everything not matched by a more specific rule below.
# This owner reviews ordinary Atlas/ knowledge contributions.
*                     @org/company-brain-maintainers

# The shared standard: schema and shared SOPs. Governance changes land here
# and deserve the strictest review. Point this at the people who own the
# rules for the whole company, not just any maintainer.
/AI-OS/Schemas/       @org/standards-owners
/AI-OS/SOPs/          @org/standards-owners

# The federation and OKF tooling. Changes here affect every vault's sync
# and validation, so route them to whoever maintains the scripts.
/.github/             @org/company-brain-maintainers
